Class EdgeClassification

public class EdgeClassification
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

This enumeration defines values for a Tree Edge, a Back Edge and a Forward Edge. Edge definitions taken from: "Introduction to Algorithms" by Thomas Corman, Charles Leiserson and Ronald Rivest, pg. 482.

Field Detail

TREE_EDGE

public static EdgeClassification TREE_EDGE
An edge in the depth-first forest G. Edge(u,v) is a tree edge if v was first discovered by exploring edge (u,v).

BACK_EDGE

public static EdgeClassification BACK_EDGE
An edge (u,v) connecting a vertex u to an ancestor v in a depth first tree. Self loops are considered to be back edges.

FORWARD_EDGE

public static EdgeClassification FORWARD_EDGE
An nontree edge (u, v) connecting a vertex u to a decendant v in a depth-first tree.
